html","id":"installation","dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"Installation","title":"Useful pipe-like operators to standard functions","text":"can install development version LSutils GitHub :","code":"# install.packages(\"pak\") pak::pak(\"saltylubik/LSutils\")"},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/index.html","id":"example","dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"Example","title":"Useful pipe-like operators to standard functions","text":"Simple use case package.","code":"library(LSutils)  ## basic example code  # %nin% operator - negate %in% x <- c(\"a\", \"b\", \"c\") x %nin% letters #> [1] FALSE FALSE FALSE  # %p% operator - paste0 which concatenates LHS and RHS with underscore, can be chained \"a\" %p% \"b\" #> [1] \"a_b\" \"a\" %p% \"b\" %p% \"c\" #> [1] \"a_b_c\"  # %g% operator - grepl where LHS is pattern and RHS is character vector where matches are sought \"a\" %g% c(\"abc\", \"a\") #> [1] TRUE TRUE  # %col% operator - apply function to columns of a matrix or data.frame iris[,1:4] %col% function(x) mean(x, na.rm = T) #> Sepal.Length  Sepal.Width Petal.Length  Petal.Width  #>     5.843333     3.057333     3.758000     1.199333  # %row% operator - apply function to rows of a matrix or data.frame iris[,1:4] %row% function(x) mean(x, na.rm = T) #>   [1] 2.550 2.375 2.350 2.350 2.550 2.850 2.425 2.525 2.225 2.400 2.700 2.500 #>  [13] 2.325 2.125 2.800 3.000 2.750 2.575 2.875 2.675 2.675 2.675 2.350 2.650 #>  [25] 2.575 2.450 2.600 2.600 2.550 2.425 2.425 2.675 2.725 2.825 2.425 2.400 #>  [37] 2.625 2.500 2.225 2.550 2.525 2.100 2.275 2.675 2.800 2.375 2.675 2.350 #>  [49] 2.675 2.475 4.075 3.900 4.100 3.275 3.850 3.575 3.975 2.900 3.850 3.300 #>  [61] 2.875 3.650 3.300 3.775 3.350 3.900 3.650 3.400 3.600 3.275 3.925 3.550 #>  [73] 3.800 3.700 3.725 3.850 3.950 4.100 3.725 3.200 3.200 3.150 3.400 3.850 #>  [85] 3.600 3.875 4.000 3.575 3.500 3.325 3.425 3.775 3.400 2.900 3.450 3.525 #>  [97] 3.525 3.675 2.925 3.475 4.525 3.875 4.525 4.150 4.375 4.825 3.400 4.575 #> [109] 4.200 4.850 4.200 4.075 4.350 3.800 4.025 4.300 4.200 5.100 4.875 3.675 #> [121] 4.525 3.825 4.800 3.925 4.450 4.550 3.900 3.950 4.225 4.400 4.550 5.025 #> [133] 4.250 3.925 3.925 4.775 4.425 4.200 3.900 4.375 4.450 4.350 3.875 4.550 #> [145] 4.550 4.300 3.925 4.175 4.325 3.950"},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-col-grapes.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Apply on columns operator — %col%","title":"Apply on columns operator — %col%","text":"Apply columns operator","code":""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-col-grapes.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Apply on columns operator — %col%","text":"","code":"x %col% y"},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-col-grapes.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Apply on columns operator — %col%","text":"x matrix data.frame. y name function apply columns - can define .","code":""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-col-grapes.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Apply on columns operator — %col%","text":"Returns vector array list values obtained applying function columns.","code":""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-col-grapes.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Apply on columns operator — %col%","text":"","code":"# can be used like: iris[,c(1:4)] %col% function(x) mean(x, na.rm = TRUE) #> Sepal.Length  Sepal.Width Petal.Length  Petal.Width  #>     5.843333     3.057333     3.758000     1.199333   # or like this: iris[,c(1:4)] %col% sum #> Sepal.Length  Sepal.Width Petal.Length  Petal.Width  #>        876.5        458.6        563.7        179.9"},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-g-grapes.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Grepl operator — %g%","title":"Grepl operator — %g%","text":"Grepl operator","code":""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-g-grapes.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Grepl operator — %g%","text":"","code":"x %g% y"},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-g-grapes.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Grepl operator — %g%","text":"x pattern: character string look . y character vector matches sought.","code":""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-g-grapes.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Grepl operator — %g%","text":"logical vector.","code":""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-g-grapes.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Grepl operator — %g%","text":"","code":"# Returns TRUE x <- \"h\" y <- \"hello\" x %g% y #> [1] TRUE"},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-nin-grapes.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Negate in operator — %nin%","title":"Negate in operator — %nin%","text":"Negate operator","code":""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-nin-grapes.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Negate in operator — %nin%","text":"","code":"x %nin% y"},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-nin-grapes.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Negate in operator — %nin%","text":"x vector NULL: values matched. y vector NULL: values matched .","code":""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-nin-grapes.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Negate in operator — %nin%","text":"logical vector.","code":""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-nin-grapes.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Negate in operator — %nin%","text":"","code":"# Negates the %in% operator - returns c(FALSE, FALSE, FALSE) x <- c(\"a\", \"b\", \"c\") x %nin% letters #> [1] FALSE FALSE FALSE"},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-p-grapes.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"paste0 operator with underscore separator — %p%","title":"paste0 operator with underscore separator — %p%","text":"paste0 operator underscore separator","code":""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-p-grapes.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"paste0 operator with underscore separator — %p%","text":"","code":"x %p% y"},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-p-grapes.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"paste0 operator with underscore separator — %p%","text":"x character string. y character string.","code":""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-p-grapes.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"paste0 operator with underscore separator — %p%","text":"character string.","code":""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-p-grapes.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"paste0 operator with underscore separator — %p%","text":"","code":"# return \"hello_world\" x <- \"hello\" y <- \"world\" x %p% y #> [1] \"hello_world\"  # you can chain them - a_b_c letters[1] %p% letters[2] %p% letters[3] #> [1] \"a_b_c\""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-row-grapes.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Apply on rows operator — %row%","title":"Apply on rows operator — %row%","text":"Apply rows operator","code":""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-row-grapes.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Apply on rows operator — %row%","text":"","code":"x %row% y"},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-row-grapes.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Apply on rows operator — %row%","text":"x matrix data.frame. y name function apply rows - can define .","code":""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-row-grapes.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Apply on rows operator — %row%","text":"Returns vector array list values obtained applying function rows.","code":""},{"path":"https://saltylubik.github.io/LSutils/reference/grapes-row-grapes.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Apply on rows operator — %row%","text":"","code":"# can be used like: iris[,c(1:4)] %row% function(x) mean(x, na.rm = TRUE) #>   [1] 2.550 2.375 2.350 2.350 2.550 2.850 2.425 2.525 2.225 2.400 2.700 2.500 #>  [13] 2.325 2.125 2.800 3.000 2.750 2.575 2.875 2.675 2.675 2.675 2.350 2.650 #>  [25] 2.575 2.450 2.600 2.600 2.550 2.425 2.425 2.675 2.725 2.825 2.425 2.400 #>  [37] 2.625 2.500 2.225 2.550 2.525 2.100 2.275 2.675 2.800 2.375 2.675 2.350 #>  [49] 2.675 2.475 4.075 3.900 4.100 3.275 3.850 3.575 3.975 2.900 3.850 3.300 #>  [61] 2.875 3.650 3.300 3.775 3.350 3.900 3.650 3.400 3.600 3.275 3.925 3.550 #>  [73] 3.800 3.700 3.725 3.850 3.950 4.100 3.725 3.200 3.200 3.150 3.400 3.850 #>  [85] 3.600 3.875 4.000 3.575 3.500 3.325 3.425 3.775 3.400 2.900 3.450 3.525 #>  [97] 3.525 3.675 2.925 3.475 4.525 3.875 4.525 4.150 4.375 4.825 3.400 4.575 #> [109] 4.200 4.850 4.200 4.075 4.350 3.800 4.025 4.300 4.200 5.100 4.875 3.675 #> [121] 4.525 3.825 4.800 3.925 4.450 4.550 3.900 3.950 4.225 4.400 4.550 5.025 #> [133] 4.250 3.925 3.925 4.775 4.425 4.200 3.900 4.375 4.450 4.350 3.875 4.550 #> [145] 4.550 4.300 3.925 4.175 4.325 3.950  # or like this: iris[,c(1:4)] %row% sum #>   [1] 10.2  9.5  9.4  9.4 10.2 11.4  9.7 10.1  8.9  9.6 10.8 10.0  9.3  8.5 11.2 #>  [16] 12.0 11.0 10.3 11.5 10.7 10.7 10.7  9.4 10.6 10.3  9.8 10.4 10.4 10.2  9.7 #>  [31]  9.7 10.7 10.9 11.3  9.7  9.6 10.5 10.0  8.9 10.2 10.1  8.4  9.1 10.7 11.2 #>  [46]  9.5 10.7  9.4 10.7  9.9 16.3 15.6 16.4 13.1 15.4 14.3 15.9 11.6 15.4 13.2 #>  [61] 11.5 14.6 13.2 15.1 13.4 15.6 14.6 13.6 14.4 13.1 15.7 14.2 15.2 14.8 14.9 #>  [76] 15.4 15.8 16.4 14.9 12.8 12.8 12.6 13.6 15.4 14.4 15.5 16.0 14.3 14.0 13.3 #>  [91] 13.7 15.1 13.6 11.6 13.8 14.1 14.1 14.7 11.7 13.9 18.1 15.5 18.1 16.6 17.5 #> [106] 19.3 13.6 18.3 16.8 19.4 16.8 16.3 17.4 15.2 16.1 17.2 16.8 20.4 19.5 14.7 #> [121] 18.1 15.3 19.2 15.7 17.8 18.2 15.6 15.8 16.9 17.6 18.2 20.1 17.0 15.7 15.7 #> [136] 19.1 17.7 16.8 15.6 17.5 17.8 17.4 15.5 18.2 18.2 17.2 15.7 16.7 17.3 15.8"}]
